  "prompt": "What are some good NGOs working in the field of children's education in India?",
  "response": "Here are several reputable NGOs working in children's education in India:\n\n1. Pratham Education Foundation\n- Large national organization\n- Focus on improving quality of education\n- Conducts learning assessments and literacy programs\n\n2. Teach For India\n- Recruits and trains young professionals as teachers\n- Works in low-income schools\n- Aims to eliminate educational inequality\n\n3. Save the Children India\n- Provides education support in rural and urban areas\n- Focuses on child rights and quality education\n- Runs multiple educational programs\n\n4. Akanksha Foundation\n- Works with children from low-income communities\n- Provides holistic education and skill development\n- Runs schools and after-school learning centers\n\n5. Room to Read\n- Focuses on literacy and girls' education\n- Establishes libraries and publishes children's books\n- Works in multiple Indian states\n\n6. CRY (Child Rights and You)\n- Advocates for children's rights\n- Supports education programs\n- Works across multiple states\n\n7. Smile Foundation\n- Provides educational support to underprivileged children\n- Runs school support and scholarship programs\n- Focuses on Girl Child Education\n\nThese organizations have proven track records and demonstrate significant impact in improving children's education in India.",
